# Chasing Your Tail NG (CYT-NG) Desktop Launcher
#
# Installed from https://github.com/ArgeliusLabs/Chasing-Your-Tail-NG
# "MUCH Improved version of the Python Chasing Your Tail Tool"
#
# Provides a desktop icon + clean launcher that starts the project's
# enhanced GUI (cyt_gui.py) with all its buttons:
#   - Check System Status
#   - Create / Delete Ignore Lists (secure JSON format)
#   - START CHASING YOUR TAIL (core real-time monitor)
#   - Analyze Logs (probe_analyzer)
#   - Surveillance Analysis (surveillance_analyzer.py + GPS + KML)
#
# The launcher follows the established pattern in this environment
# (pkexec + zenity preflights + xhost for X11 + root GUI) used by
# Wifite, WiFi-Pentest-Kit, Jam-Fi, etc.
#
# After launch you get a nice 800x480 dark UI (matrix green logs)
# tailored for small screens / BlackHat-style demos.
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Requires Kismet .kismet database files (live or historical).
# - Full real-time "chasing" needs a Wi-Fi adapter in monitor mode + Kismet running.
# - See /home/will/bin/cyt-ng/README.md and SETUP.md for details.
# - First-run security migration is handled automatically (idempotent).
# - Outputs land in the project dir under logs/, reports/, kml_files/, etc.
#
# For legitimate security research, personal safety, and authorized testing only.
# Users are responsible for complying with applicable laws.
